#Base service messages
base.service.title     = Check your VAT flat rate
base.errorSummary      = There are errors on this page

##  COMMON  ##
common.continue = Continue
common.year                       = year
common.quarter                    = quarter

## Errors ##
error.required                     = This field is required
error.real                         = Enter a number without commas, for example 10000.00
error.twoDecimalPlaces             = The amount you''ve entered has too many decimal places
error.negative                     = Enter an amount that''s £0 or more
error.moreThanMaximumTurnover      = Enter an amount less than £9,999,999,999.98

## Technical Errors ##
techError.title                    = Technical Error
techError.heading                  = Sorry, there''s been a problem
techError.para.1                   = You''ll need to start your calculation again.
techError.startAgain               = Start again

## VAT return period page ##
vatReturnPeriod.title               = Enter your VAT return details
vatReturnPeriod.heading             = How often do you do your VAT returns?
vatReturnPeriod.para.1              = If you''re not VAT registered or you''re just getting an estimate, you can choose either option.
vatReturnPeriod.para.2              = If you''re thinking of joining the Flat Rate scheme, select annually.
vatReturnPeriod.option.annual       = Annually
vatReturnPeriod.option.quarter      = Quarterly

## Turnover page  ##
turnover.title                      = Enter your turnover
turnover.heading                    = Enter your turnover for the {0} including VAT
turnover.para.1                     = This is the total sales of all goods and services. If you''re estimating, give realistic figures.

## Cost of goods page ##
costOfGoods.title                   = Cost of goods
costOfGoods.heading                 = Enter your cost of goods for the {0} including VAT
costOfGoods.para.1                  = Goods are moveable items or materials exclusively used in your business. You can also include gas and electricity. If you''re estimating, give realistic figures.
costOfGoods.doNotInclude            = Don''t include:
costOfGoods.bullet.1                = business expenses like travel, accommodation and food
costOfGoods.bullet.2                = rent
costOfGoods.bullet.3                = internet and phone bills
costOfGoods.bullet.4                = accountancy fees
costOfGoods.bullet.5                = training, memberships and subscriptions
costOfGoods.bullet.6                = software unless it''s on a disc
costOfGoods.bullet.7                = capital items like office equipment such as laptops, mobile phones and tablets
costOfGoods.bullet.8                = other services like solicitors or agents fees

